4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Currently, certain income is exempt from state
6 income taxes.
7 This bill would exempt the first $5,000 earned
8 from drill pay by a member of the Alabama National
9 Guard from state income tax.
10 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
11 technical revisions to update the existing code
12 language to current style.
13
14
15 A BILL
16 TO BE ENTITLED
17 AN ACT
18
19 Relating to exemptions from state income taxation; to
20 amend Section 40-18-19, Code of Alabama 1975; to exempt the
21 first $5,000 of taxable income earned from inactive duty
22 training from state income tax for individuals that serve in
23 the Alabama National Guard; and to make nonsubstantive,
24 technical revisions to update the existing code language to
25 current style.
26 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
27 Section 1. Section 40-18-19, Code of Alabama 1975, is
28 amended to read as follows:
